@@ What is a ReplicaSet?
=> A ReplicaSet ensures that a specified number of Pod replicas are always running.

Example:

Desired State = 3 Pods
Running Pods = 3

If one Pod dies:

Desired State = 3
Running Pods = 2

ReplicaSet automatically creates:

New Pod = 1
Running Pods = 3

@@ This is called ==> Self-Healing

################################################
########## Create ReplicaSet ################

[root@k8s-control01 ~]# replicaset.yml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: ReplicaSet
metadata:
  name: nginx-rs
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx

@@ Deploy:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl apply -f replicaset.yml

@@ Verify:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl get rs

@@ Expected:
NAME       DESIRED CURRENT READY
nginx-rs   3       3       3

@@ Check Pods:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl get pods

@@ Example:
nginx-rs-x1abc
nginx-rs-y2def
nginx-rs-z3ghi

@@ Understanding Labels & Selectors
@@ ReplicaSet tracks Pods using:

@@ matchLabels:
  app: nginx
and
labels:
  app: nginx

These must match.

@@ Think:
ReplicaSet = Manager
Labels = Employee ID Card
Selector = Employee Database Search

